data.name: lblMasterlvllistHelp.ToolTip
data.value:
CHKP. (checkpoint) If checked, the lvl will end with a checkpoint. If unchecked, the lvl will not end with a checkpoint and will flow into the next lvl.
P+ (play+) If checked, the lvl will appear when playing in Play+. If unchecked, it will be left out. This is useful for tutorial levels in Play, and then removing them for Play+.
ISO. (isolate) When checked, only isolated levels will play in game. Useful for testing specific sublevels without replaying the entire thing.

data.name: label20.ToolTip
data.value:
Editing works the same way as the leaf editor. You can use float (decimals) between 0 and 1 to change a sample/loop track volume throughout the lvl. 0 = off
This is useful to make certain loop tracks quieter so they don't drown out other sounds at specific times.

data.name: lblGatebuckethelp.ToolTip
data.value:
!! RANDOM ONLY WORKS WITH BOSS SPIROGRAPH !!
When enabled, each boss phase will select a random lvl from its respective "bucket". Phase 1 (0) will only take from bucket 0, phase 2 (1) only from bucket 1, and so on.
Buckets need a minimum 1 lvl and maximum 4 lvls.
There are 4 buckets. If a bucket has no lvl assigned, the phase defaults to bucket 0.

data.name: label46.ToolTip
data.value: Interpolation type between beat values. Higher interpolation = smoother transitions/curves, but higher intensity calculation. Can decrease FPS. THIS AFFECTS IN-GAME ONLY. NOT THIS EDITOR'S INTERPOLATION CALC.

data.name: label8.ToolTip
data.value:
Whether the value changes every beat (step = TRUE)(utilizing default on empty beats), or interoplates between set data points (step = FALSE)
Only useful for Trait types of kTraitFloat and kTraitColor

data.name: btnTrackPlayback.ToolTipText
data.value:
***CURRENTLY BUGGY. SKIPS BEATS SOMETIMES*** Click to playback the entire leaf. Plays these objects in time: -Thumps -Turns -Bars and Rings -Jumps -Millipedes -Samples
